Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_quiet_attacker(25.10)                            set_quiet_attacker(25.10)

Name
       set_quiet_attacker  - Specifies one or more coupled nets as non-attack-
       ers (silent) for the delay and glitch analysis of a given victim net

Syntax
       set_quiet_attacker

       [-help]

       [-analysis_type {early | late}]

       [-attacker <string>]

       [-transition {rise | fall}]

       [-victim <string>]

       [-view <string>]

       Specifies one or more coupled nets as non-attackers  (silent)  for  the
       delay and glitch analysis of a given victim net.

       You can run the update_glitch or update_timing command and view the re-
       sults in the report_noise or report_timing command output.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -analysis_type {early | late}
              Specifies  the analysis type for which the attackers will be as-
              sumed quiet. If no value is specified, attackers are skipped for
              both early/late analysis.

       -attacker <string>
              Specifies the attackers which should be  made  quiet  for  given
              victim  net(s).  If no attacker is specified, all the aggressors
              of given victim(s) will be ignored.

              Note: If no victim is specified,  the  specified  attackers  are
              made quiet for all victim nets in the design.

       -transition {rise | fall}
              Specifies  the victim transition for which attackers will be as-
              sumed quiet. If no value is specified, attackers are skipped for
              both rise and  fall transitions of the victim net.

       -victim <string>
              Specifies a list of victim nets for which  attackers  should  be
              made  quiet.  Specific  attackers  can be skipped using the -at-
              tacker option of this command. If the -attacker  option  is  not
              specified,  all  the attackers of the given nets are made silent
              and SI analysis will not be performed on these nets.

              Note: If this option is not specified, the  attackers  specified
              in  the  -attacker option are made quiet for all the nets in the
              design.

       -view <string>
              Specifies the view for which attackers should be made quiet.  If
              no view is specified, attackers are assumed quiet in all views

Examples
       Consider  a design having an attacker agg to victim nets vic1 and vic2.
       The following command sets the attacker agg as quiet for both the  vic-
       tim nets vic1 and vic2.

       set_quiet_attacker -attacker {agg}

              * The  following  command  sets the attackers A1 and A2 as quiet
                when V1 is rising during late analysis.

                set_quiet_attacker -victim V1 -attacker A1 A2 -transition rise
                -analysis_type late

              * The following command sets the attacker A1 quiet for victim V1
                in the analysis view VIEW1. In this case, A1 may  be  a  valid
                attacker  during SI analysis for victim V1 in views other than
                VIEW1.

                set_quiet_attacker -victim V1 -attacker A1 -view {VIEW1}

       Consider a design having victim vic with attackers agg1 and agg2:

              * The following command sets both the attackers agg1 and agg2 as
                quiet for the victim net vic.

                set_quiet_attacker -victim {vic}

              * The following command sets the attacker agg1 as quiet for  the
                given victim net vic

                set_quiet_attacker -attacker {agg1} -victim {vic}

